#: ../../P/priority-interrupt.rst:5
msgid "priority interrupt"
msgstr "priority interrupt"

#: ../../P/priority-interrupt.rst:7
msgid "n\\."
msgstr "名詞"

#: ../../P/priority-interrupt.rst:9
msgid ""
"[from the hardware term] Describes any stimulus compelling enough to yank "
"one right out of :ref:`hack-mode`\\. Classically used to describe being "
"dragged away by an :ref:`SO` for immediate sex, but may also refer to more "
"mundane interruptions such as a fire alarm going off in the near vicinity. "
"Also called an :ref:`NMI` (non-maskable interrupt), especially in PC-land."
msgstr ""
"[ハードウェア用語から]人を\\ :ref:`hack-mode`\\ "
"からぐいと引き出すほど抗いがたいあらゆる刺激を表す。古典的には、即座のセックスのために\\ :ref:`SO`\\ "
"に連れ去られることを表すのに使われるが、近所で火災報知器が鳴るといったもっとありふれた中断を指すこともある。特にPC界隈では、\\ "
":ref:`NMI`\\ (non-maskable interrupt、マスク不可能割り込み)とも呼ばれる。"
